  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam will provide technical input on emergency WASH response activities to improve access to and utilization of safe water supplies and sanitation facilities and CARE&apos;s supporting interventions will include community mobilization and a public health information and education campaign (IEC). The interface of these components will augment delivery of intensive hygiene promotion activities with particular attention to the needs, participation and representation of women and girls. Specific attention will be given to ensure the entire intervention is undertaken through a responsive, inclusive and gender and disability-sensitive lens.</narrative>
  </description>
